            <html:p><fr:link href="/jms-00BN/" title="Event structure" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00BN/" display-uri="jms-00BN" type="local">Event structures</fr:link> are the same thing as prime algebraic domains; on objects, this has been proved many times, but I could only find the correct notion of morphism in a <fr:link href="/abbes-2006/" title="A Cartesian closed category of event structures with quotients" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/abbes-2006/" display-uri="abbes-2006" type="local">paper of Abbes</fr:link>.</html:p>
